SUMMARY:MIG Welding\, GMAW(Gas Metal Arc Welding)
DESCRIPTION:Learn to stick metal together using Metal Inert Gas Welding at Site 3!\n\n\nIntroducing the Mig process class! This class will expose you to the fundamentals of MIG welding. Come see why this process is the choice for quick projects\, artists\, production needs\, thin gauge materials and the backbone of the automotive industry. \nSafety requirements: Long sleeve clothing made from natural materials (old cotton clothing you don’t mind getting dirty) is mandatory. Safety googles are provided and can acomodate prescription glasses(must be worn the duration of the class\, can be purchased at Dollar store)\, wear closed toe shoes\, no jewelry\, hair must be tied back and/or have a cap or bandanna on. \nPARTICIPANTS MUST BE 18 YEARS OF AGE OR OLDER. \nIF YOU REQUIRE ACCOMMODATIONS\, CONTACT INFO@SITE3.CA BEFORE PURCHASING YOUR TICKET. WE WILL DO OUR BEST TO HOST YOU. \nREFUNDS WILL ONLY BE GIVEN IF YOU EMAIL INFO@SITE3.CA WITH MORE THAN 72 HOURS REMAINING UNTIL THE CLASS. ALL OTHER REQUESTS WILL BE DEALT WITH AT THE ORGANISATION’S DISCRETION AND REFUNDS MAY NOT BE GIVEN.
URL:https://www.site3.ca/event/mig-welding-gmawgas-metal-arc-welding/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.site3.ca/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/5929_image.jpg
END:VEVENT
